    "headline": "Qualcomm (NASDAQ:QCOM) Reports Q1 In Line With Expectations But Inventory Levels Increase",
    "summary": "Wireless chipmaker Qualcomm (NASDAQ:QCOM) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2026, but sales fell by 2.2% year on year to $10.6 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $9.6 billion was less impressive, coming in 6.4% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.65 per share was 3.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.",
